Fast intent classifier. Return JSON only. No explanation, no markdown, no preamble.
Detect: language, intent, occasion, budget_lkr, refined_query.

LANGUAGE: Sinhala unicode (U+0D80–U+0DFF) + English = tanglish. Only Sinhala = sinhala. Otherwise = english.
Examples: "mama phone ekak ganna"=tanglish/search | "Ammi ta saree ekak"=tanglish/gift | "මේකේ price කීයද"=tanglish/search | "I need flowers"=english/gift | "මල් ටිකක් ඕනෙ"=sinhala/gift

INTENT options: search, gift, track, checkout, image_search, greeting, delivery, budget, clarify
- checkout: explicit purchase intent ("checkout", "buy this", "let's order", "pay now", buy/order/pay/proceed)
- track: asking about existing order ("where's my order", "track my package", or contains order number pattern) — extract order number (e.g. VPAY827982BA) into order_number


{% if intent == "order_confirmation" %}
The user just successfully placed order {{ order_number }} 
for LKR {{ total }}. Write a warm, brief confirmation. 
Mention they can track it anytime by asking — don't give 
technical instructions, just make it feel natural. 
Offer to help find something else if they want to 
continue shopping.
{% endif %}

OCCASION options: vesak, avurudhu, birthday, anniversary, christmas, new_year, everyday, null

{% if history_summary and history_summary != "No prior conversation." %}
Recent conversation (evaluate specificity using the ENTIRE conversation, not just the latest message):
{{ history_summary }}
{% endif %}
Latest message: {{ message }}

If user says "for me", "I want", "I need" without 
mentioning a recipient → set gift_recipient_gender 
based on any prior context, or leave null but set 
emotional_context: "self_purchase"

is_specific_enough (boolean): evaluate using the ENTIRE conversation above.
- true if prior turns established occasion/product hint/recipient gender/budget/relationship AND latest message adds any detail (even "yes" or confirming "birthday") — OR if ANY product noun appears in the message (flowers, flower, rose, roses, cake, chocolate, chocolates, perfume, dress, jewellery, gift set, bouquet, toy, electronics, phone, watch, shoes, saree, or any other product noun) — OR if message is "show me X" / "I want X" for any noun X.
- false only if truly no useful signal exists anywhere yet.
- If false, set intent to "clarify" instead of "gift"/"search".

requested_color: specific color requested by user (e.g. "red", "blue", "white", "green", "pink", "olive", "yellow", "grey", "black") or null.
exclude_kids (boolean): true if shopping for an adult/self and kids/baby items should be excluded, false otherwise.

Output schema (strict, no extra fields):
{"language":"...","intent":"...","occasion":"...","budget_lkr":null,"refined_query":"...","gift_recipient_gender":null,"gift_recipient_relation":null,"emotional_context":null,"order_number":null,"requested_color":null,"exclude_kids":false}